def draw_histograms(df, variables, n_rows, n_cols, n_bins):
    fig=plt.figure()
    for i, var_name in enumerate(variables):
        ax=fig.add_subplot(n_rows,n_cols,i+1)
        df[var_name].hist(bins=n_bins,ax=ax)
        ax.set_title(var_name)
    fig.tight_layout()  
    plt.show()

# Correlation between attributes in the dataset
PAY variables are the strongest predictors by default, followed by the LIMIT_BAL and PAY_AMT .

X = credit.drop(['default payment next month'],axis=1)
X.corrwith(credit['default payment next month']).plot.bar(figsize = (20, 10), title = "Correlation", 
                                        fontsize = 15,rot = 90, grid = True)
Outliers among numerical features can be seen from above. As they might be significant in term of target output, we gonna keep them during our modeling process.
Some categories are mislabeled or undocumented.Data cleaning needed before proceed to next step
credit.EDUCATION.value_counts() # 1 = graduate school; 2 = university; 3 = high school; 0, 4, 5, 6 = others

The 0 in MARRIAGE to be categorized as 'Other' (thus 3).
